# Verify deploys end-to-end

A deploy is not done until the **user-facing flow** works. Health checks (`/api/parts` returning 200) are necessary but not sufficient.

## After every deploy, verify through CloudFront

The canonical URL is `https://d1n87lopz9qnnf.cloudfront.net/` — test there, not against the raw EC2 IP.

```bash
# 1. Health check (necessary but not sufficient)
make check-health

# 2. Verify RENDER_URL points to CloudFront HTTPS (not raw EC2 HTTP)
curl -s https://d1n87lopz9qnnf.cloudfront.net/index.html | grep '__RENDER_URL__'
# Must show https://d1n87lopz9qnnf.cloudfront.net/

# 3. Test preview flow end-to-end through CloudFront
JOB=$(curl -s -X POST https://d1n87lopz9qnnf.cloudfront.net/api/preview \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"params":{}}')
JOB_ID=$(echo "$JOB" | python3 -c "import json,sys; print(json.load(sys.stdin)['job_id'])")
sleep 10
curl -s "https://d1n87lopz9qnnf.cloudfront.net/api/jobs/$JOB_ID" | python3 -c "
import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin)
print('status:', d['status'], '| stls:', len(d.get('result',{}).get('stl_urls',{})) if d.get('result') else 0)
"
# Must show: status: complete | stls: 8
```

## Common post-deploy failures

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
|---------|-------|-----|
| "Render server is offline" | CORS origin mismatch or mixed content | Check `static_site_url` env var has `https://` prefix |
| "Preview queued..." forever | Route not covered by CloudFront behavior | Ensure route uses `/api/` prefix; check `infra/static.tf` |
| Stale content after deploy | CloudFront cache | Run `aws cloudfront create-invalidation --distribution-id E6P6W4VNARX5W --paths "/*"` |
| Container won't start | Architecture mismatch (arm64 vs amd64) | Use `make build` (defaults to `--platform linux/amd64`) |
| `docker pull` fails on EC2 | ECR token expired | `deploy-ec2` target now handles this; if manual, run `aws ecr get-login-password` first |

## Invalidate CloudFront after static deploys

Always invalidate after `make deploy-static`:

```bash
aws cloudfront create-invalidation --distribution-id E6P6W4VNARX5W --paths "/*"
```

Consider adding this to the `deploy-static` target itself.
